narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Technical skills in manual shooting, editing in camera raw and photoshop, and printing.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course could use much, much more structure. Weekly assignments, for example, would have been very helpful to keep students shooting regularly and thinking about photography carefully. I also would have appreciated learning more skills on photoshop, and receiving written instructions/guides to the skills we did learn, which were only gone over once and hard to remember and reconstruct on our own. High points were slideshows of "the greats" -- Diane Arbus, Lee Friedlander, etc. -- and field trips to look at collections at the YUAG.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes- great course and Zak is a great professor. It is interesting, engaging, and makes you see the world in a new way, in addition to developing useful photo taking, editing, and printing skills. Would highly recommend!
Zak is new to teaching, and so while he's a wonderful person and talented photographer, the course structure for this section of Intro Digital needs some revising.
